    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Slice your <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, increase to a high heat and add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>gochujang paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5 min further, until thickened and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>udon noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside to soak for 4-5 min</p><p>Tip: Gently separate the noodles with a fork!</p><p>Drain the soaked noodles</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bolognese has thickened, add your <strong>soaked udon noodles</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up until the noodles are coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>one pan gochujang bolognese with udon noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-gochujang-lean-pork-bolognese-with-udon-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pan gochujang bolognese with udon noodles </strong>and top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
